## рџ—„пёЏ Database Schema (Prisma / SQLite)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    User {
        String id PK
        String name
        String email
        String password
        String role
        Int currentStreak
        Int longestStreak
        DateTime lastLogin
    }
    Course {
        String id PK
        String title
        String description
        String teacherId FK
    }
    Enrollment {
        String id PK
        String userId FK
        String courseId FK
        DateTime enrolledAt
    }
    Quiz {
        String id PK
        String title
        String courseId FK
        DateTime startDate
        DateTime endDate
        Int timeLimit
    }
    Question {
        String id PK
        String quizId FK
        String text
        String options
        String correctAnswer
    }
    QuizAttempt {
        String id PK
        String userId FK
        String quizId FK
        Int score
        Int total
    }
    Announcement {
        String id PK
        String title
        String content
        String courseId FK
        String authorId FK
    }

    User ||--o{ Course : "teaches"
    User ||--o{ Enrollment : "has"
    User ||--o{ QuizAttempt : "makes"
    User ||--o{ Announcement : "authors"
    Course ||--o{ Enrollment : "has"
    Course ||--o{ Quiz : "has"
    Course ||--o{ Announcement : "has"
    Quiz ||--o{ Question : "has"
    Quiz ||--o{ QuizAttempt : "has"
```

---

## рџ”ђ Authentication & Roles

- **JWT-based** auth вЂ” token stored in `localStorage`
- **3 Roles:**
  - `STUDENT` вЂ” Enroll in courses, take quizzes, view performance
  - `TEACHER` вЂ” Create courses, create quizzes, add/view students, post announcements
  - `ADMIN` вЂ” Full platform access
- **Login Streak** вЂ” Tracked daily via `lastLogin`, `currentStreak`, `longestStreak` on the [User](file:///c:/Users/gnana/OneDrive/Desktop/KLU/projects-gnana/educore/frontend/src/services/apiServices.ts#30-34) model

---

## рџЊђ API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | No | Create account |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | No | Login + get JWT |
| GET | `/api/courses` | No | List all courses |
| GET | `/api/courses/:id` | No | Course detail |
| POST | `/api/courses` | TEACHER/ADMIN | Create course |
| PUT | `/api/courses/:id` | TEACHER/ADMIN | Update course |
| DELETE | `/api/courses/:id` | TEACHER/ADMIN | Delete course |
| POST | `/api/enrollments` | Any | Enroll in course |
| GET | `/api/enrollments/my-courses` | Any | My enrolled courses |
| GET | `/api/enrollments/my-performance` | Any | My quiz scores |
| GET | `/api/enrollments/course/:id/students` | TEACHER | Students in course |
| POST | `/api/enrollments/course/:id/add-student` | TEACHER | Add student by email |
| GET | `/api/quizzes/course/:id` | Any | Quizzes for a course |
| GET | `/api/quizzes/:id` | Any | Quiz detail |
| POST | `/api/quizzes` | TEACHER | Create quiz |
| POST | `/api/quizzes/submit` | Any | Submit quiz attempt |
| GET | `/api/announcements` | Any | All announcements |
| POST | `/api/announcements` | TEACHER | Create announcement |
| **POST** | **`/api/ai/chat`** | **Any (logged in)** | **[NEW] AI course chatbot** |

---

## рџ¤– AI Chatbot Feature (New Addition)

The chatbot appears as a **floating glowing icon** at the bottom-right of every course detail page. When clicked, it opens an animated chat panel. It uses the course's context (title, description, instructor, quizzes, announcements) to answer student doubts intelligently.

**Flow:**
```
Student types question
       в†“
Frontend sends: { message, courseContext } в†’ POST /api/ai/chat
       в†“
Backend builds system prompt with course context
       в†“
Calls Google Gemini 1.5 Flash API
       в†“
Returns { reply: string }
       в†“
Chat bubble rendered in UI
```

**Required:** `GEMINI_API_KEY` in [backend/.env](file:///c:/Users/gnana/OneDrive/Desktop/KLU/projects-gnana/educore/backend/.env)

---

## рџљЂ Deployment Guide (Step-by-Step)

### Option A вЂ” Easiest: Render (Free Tier)

#### 1. Prepare Backend for Production

Switch the database from **SQLite в†’ PostgreSQL** (SQLite is not suitable for hosted servers):

```bash
# In backend/
npm install @prisma/client
```

Update [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/gnana/OneDrive/Desktop/KLU/projects-gnana/educore/backend/prisma/schema.prisma):
```prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}
```

Run migration:
```bash
npx prisma migrate deploy
```

#### 2. Backend `.env` Variables

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/educore
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here
PORT=5000
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
```

#### 3. Deploy Backend on [Render](https://render.com)

1. Push everything to GitHub
2. Create a **New Web Service** on Render
3. Connect your GitHub repo в†’ select the `backend/` folder
4. Build command: `npm install && npm run build`
5. Start command: `node dist/index.js`
6. Add all env variables in the Render dashboard
7. Also create a **PostgreSQL** database on Render (free) в†’ copy the connection URL

#### 4. Deploy Frontend on [Vercel](https://vercel.com)

1. Create a new project on Vercel
2. Connect your GitHub repo в†’ select `frontend/` as root
3. Build command: `npm run build`
4. Output directory: `dist`
5. Add env variable:
   ```
   VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.onrender.com/api
   ```
6. Update [frontend/src/services/api.ts](file:///c:/Users/gnana/OneDrive/Desktop/KLU/projects-gnana/educore/frontend/src/services/api.ts) to use:
   ```ts
   baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://localhost:5000/api'
   ```

---

### Option B вЂ” Full Control: VPS (DigitalOcean / AWS)

| Step | Details |
|---|---|
| Server | Ubuntu 22.04 Droplet (min 1GB RAM) |
| Node | Install via nvm (`nvm install 20`) |
| Database | PostgreSQL via `apt` |
| Process manager | `pm2` (`npm i -g pm2`) |
| Reverse proxy | Nginx pointing `api.yourdomain.com` в†’ port 5000 |
| SSL | Let's Encrypt via `certbot` |
| Frontend | Build with `npm run build` в†’ serve `dist/` via Nginx |

---

### Option C вЂ” Docker (Advanced)

Create a `docker-compose.yml` at root:
```yaml
version: '3.8'
services:
  db:
    image: postgres:15
    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: educore
      POSTGRES_USER: admin
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: secret
  backend:
    build: ./backend
    ports: ["5000:5000"]
    env_file: ./backend/.env
    depends_on: [db]
  frontend:
    build: ./frontend
    ports: ["3000:80"]
```

---

## вњ… Pre-Launch Checklist

- [ ] Switch SQLite в†’ PostgreSQL for production
- [ ] Set strong `JWT_SECRET` (at least 64 random chars)
- [ ] Add `GEMINI_API_KEY` to backend env
- [ ] Update frontend `VITE_API_URL` to point to deployed backend
- [ ] Enable CORS for your frontend domain in [backend/src/index.ts](file:///c:/Users/gnana/OneDrive/Desktop/KLU/projects-gnana/educore/backend/src/index.ts)
- [ ] Run `prisma migrate deploy` on production DB
- [ ] Test all 3 roles (STUDENT, TEACHER, ADMIN) end-to-end
- [ ] Test AI chatbot on a real course
- [ ] Set up a custom domain (optional but recommended)

